slug";s:38:"garage-door-not-closing-because-of-sun";s:5:"title";s:61:"How To Seal A Garage Door From The Inside Correctly Audio Mav";s:3:"alt";s:9:"audio mav";s:3:"url";s:103:"https://audiomav.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/How-to-Seal-a-Garage-Door-from-the-Inside-Correctly.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcROYvysDAp_nmg1500wHViMgLTQVZLE9YWBiQ";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:720;s:6:"height";i:1080;s:6:"source";s:73:"https://audiomav.com/how-to-seal-a-garage-door-from-the-inside-correctly/";s:6:"domain";s:12:"audiomav.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:66:{i:0;s:115:"If you notice that your garage door struggles to close on sunny days the sunlight is probably blinding the sensors.";i:1;s:71:"You can move your sensors out of the sunlight but this can be a hassle.";i:2;s:89:"This is especially true because the sun changes angles and directions throughout the day.";i:3;s:118:"Instead of maneuvering your sensors try these solutions to block the sun so that your garage will close automatically.";i:4;s:45:"Why does my garage door not close in the Sun.";i:5;s:119:"If your garage door has trouble closing on sunny days it might be because the sensors are getting blinded by the light.";i:6;s:124:"Moving your sensors out of the sun can be a pain especially since sunlight changes angles and directions throughout the day.";i:7;s:29:"It May Be Caused by Sunlight.";i:8;s:95:"Sunlight can interfere with the sensors beam and cause them to act as if an object blocks them.";i:9;s:37:"Many years ago sensors werent common.";i:10;s:56:"Nowadays for safety reasons most garage doors have them.";i:11;s:119:"If your garage door has trouble closing on sunny days it might be because the sensors are getting blinded by the light.";i:12;s:75:"Moving your sensors out of the sun can be a pain especially since sunlight.";i:13;s:98:"Whenever the is the least amount of sun it interferes with the sensor and the door will not close.";i:14;s:47:"The green light flutters when the door is open.";i:15;s:61:"I had a garage door company here that told me my garage door.";i:16;s:43:"Sometimes it worked and sometimes it didnt.";i:17;s:34:"Today it wouldnt cooperate at all.";i:18;s:35:"I even tried re-aiming the sensors.";i:19;s:141:"I was able to prove that it was the sun causing the issue by closing the door disengaging the door from the opener and activating the opener.";i:20;s:36:"It worked fine with the door closed.";i:21;s:31:"Soafter giving it some thought.";i:22;s:38:"Posted on March 17 2021 by Bandi Ruma.";i:23;s:154:"Shut a garage door when the sun shut a garage door when the sun your garage door in the summer garage door repairs opener shut a garage door when the sun.";i:24;s:62:"Sun In Your Eyes Garage Door Sensors Ncw Home Inspections Llc.";i:25;s:59:"Garage Door Won T Close In Sunlight It Might Be The Sensor.";i:26;s:56:"I have a Genie garage door opener with a 16 garage door.";i:27;s:63:"When the sun is shining brightly my garage door will not close.";i:28;s:71:"The sun light is so bright that the light cannot reach theother sensor.";i:29;s:109:"I know this is the problem because I pulled up my car to block the sun from the light beam and it would work.";i:30;s:176:"If you are having issues closing your garage door when there is a lot of sunlight shining into the garage you might need to check to see which safety sensor is in the sunlight.";i:31;s:112:"Sunlight can cause interference with garage door opener safety sensors preventing your garage door from closing.";i:32;s:104:"Garage door opener manufacturers state in the owners manual that either the sending or receiving sensor.";i:33;s:77:"Have you ever had a problem with your garage door not closing on a sunny day.";i:34;s:169:"You click the button to close the garage door and the garage door opener lights start flashing and the door doesnt move or it starts to roll down and then rolls back up.";i:35;s:45:"This is a quick tip article on how to fix it.";i:36;s:90:"The sensors have small LED lights to let you know when the signal is on and uninterrupted.";i:37;s:83:"Thats very helpful in finding out if theyre the reason your garage door wont close.";i:38;s:138:"If the light is off the sensor itself is probably off and if the light is blinking it means something is getting in the way of the signal.";i:39;s:98:"Whenever the is the least amount of sun it interferes with the sensor and the door will not close.";i:40;s:47:"The green light flutters when the door is open.";i:41;s:130:"If you notice a blinking light when your Chamberlain garage door wont close or its a sign that your door is telling you something.";i:42;s:37:"And you will find that in the manual.";i:43;s:94:"You need to count the number of blinking and refer to the troubleshooting guide of the manual.";i:44;s:110:"We do not have this issue in the winter months - even when it is in direct sun - only once it is warm outside.";i:45;s:116:"The person from Sears on the phone thought maybe the motor was over heated - but the garage itself is not very warm.";i:46;s:75:"The door has no issues going up once closed - only when we try to close it.";i:47;s:74:"When the sun hits my garage door sensors just right I cant close the door.";i:48;s:22:"Posted by 4 years ago.";i:49;s:40:"Garage Doors not closing on a sunny day.";i:50;s:31:"Is there any easy fix for this.";i:51;s:74:"When the sun hits my garage door sensors just right I cant close the door.";i:52;s:66:"I sanded all the way to metal because i didnt know why the powder.";i:53;s:140:"If your garage door opener wont close and the motor unit lights blink 10 times it usually means you have a problem with your safety sensors.";i:54;s:143:"In this video from Sears PartsDirect well show you some simple fixes like checking the garage door openers alignment and clearing obstructions.";i:55;s:12:"Aug 19 2008.";i:56;s:48:"My garage door will start to close then reverse.";i:57;s:41:"Then the opener light flashes on and off.";i:58;s:117:"Everything Ive read says this is because the safety sensors are misaligned blinded by direct sunlight or bad somehow.";i:59;s:52:"Well Ive checked the sensors and heres what I found.";i:60;s:104:"The sun also carries infrared light which you guessed it is more powerful than the light of the sensors.";i:61;s:113:"If the light of the sun surpasses the infrared sensors light the sensors might not be able to signal one another.";i:62;s:110:"This is why a garage door might stop closing if strong sunlight is shining on the eye of a garage door sensor.";i:63;s:120:"Because your garage door is receiving a notable amount of sun throughout the day the interior can become unbearably hot.";i:64;s:106:"With a lack of circulation in the enclosed space your car bikes and tools can scorch if youre not careful.";i:65;s:100:"Luckily we offer an insulation option to keep your garage cool during summer and warm during winter.";}}